      boolean ProcessFilter.hasExcludeFilter​(Path processPath)
      Returns whether or not the process with the given path has an explicit exclude filter setm i.e., an exclude filter that excludes this path only.
      This is the new implementation for the former (deprecated) ProcessConfiguration.isExclude() flag and is used to serve the according get command from nJAMS server.
      This is different from !
      boolean Configuration.hasProcess​(Path processPath)
      Returns whether or not this configuration contains a separate ProcessConfiguration for the process with the given path.
      boolean Configuration.hasProcessExcludeFilter​(Path processPath)
      Returns true only if there is a specific exclude setting for given process.
      This is not the same as Configuration.isProcessExcluded(Path) since there may be additional filters that lead to excluding this process.
      This method is mainly for processing configuration commands from nJAMS server.
      boolean Configuration.isProcessExcluded​(Path processPath)
      Returns true if the given process is excluded from processing for any reason.
      boolean ProcessFilter.isSelected​(Path processPath)
      Returns true if the given process should be processed.
      void ProcessFilter.setExcluded​(Path processPath, boolean excluded)
      Sets or removes an exclude filter for the given process depending on the exclude parameter.
      This is used for processing the according set command from nJAMS server.
      void Configuration.setProcessExcluded​(Path processPath, boolean excluded)
      Sets an exclude filter for the given process, or removes it according to the given exclude parameter.
